<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued August 03 at 4:20PM EDT until August 03 at 4:45PM EDT by NWS Atlanta</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 445 PM EDT
FOR MADISON COUNTY...
At 420 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Danielsville,
moving southeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations impacted include...
Danielsville, Comer, Colbert, Ila, Hull, Athens-Clarke County,
Pocataligo, Diamond Hill, Neese, and Paoli.
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
